The paper deals with the task of multiple people tracking in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. The proposed method uses deep learning techniques for tracklet re-identification, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep networks for joint reasoning about visual appearance and spatio-temporal properties suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve evaluating the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
